  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Coronary artery bifurcation lesion is still one of the most challenging lesion subsets in the
      field of non-surgical treatment for a stenotic coronary artery. When one stent is placed in
      the main brach, it increases the side branch's stenosis degree. However, its mechanism and
      incidence are not known. This study will be performed to search for the mechanism and
      incidence of that phenomenon.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
